    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-01-04T00:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-01-04T00:35:00-05:00" n="580"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d580">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.6363 Amiranian/5: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Merriam</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-01-04T09:00:00+03:25"
                            >January 4, 1937—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1. My 62, December 16, noon, and the Department’s 50, December 23, noon [<hi
                        rend="italic">6 p.m.</hi>]. Yesterday Hart and Clapp and the Iranian <pb
                        facs="0747" n="736" xml:id="pg_736"/> Government signed two concession
                    agreements, one relating to oil exploration and development, the other to
                    construction and operation of pipe line. Will telegraph brief summary later.</p>
                <p>It proved unnecessary to act on paragraph 3 of No. 50. Crain<note n="22"
                        xml:id="d580fn22">Earl T. Crain, Third Secretary of Legation.</note> was
                    present in a purely notarial capacity.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Merriam</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
